issues.description: The problem statement’s UML specifies addGuestStudents(int): void, but the solution implements addGuestStudents returning a boolean. This return‐type mismatch conflicts with the specification and will confuse students about the intended signature.
issues.suggested_fix: Change the solution’s addGuestStudents method signature to return void (as per the UML) and remove the boolean return statements, or alternatively update the UML and problem description to expect a boolean return if validation is desired.
